
[1]absent

   AB'SENT, a.

   1. Not present; not in company; at such a distance as to prevent
   communication. It is used also for being in a foreign country.

   A gentleman is absent on his travels.

   Absent from one another. Gen. 31:49.

   2. Heedless; inattentive to persons present, or to subjects of
   conversation in company.

   An absent man is uncivil to the company.

   3. In familiar language, not at home; as, the master of the house is
   absent. In other words, he does not wish to be disturbed by company.
